==Andorra==
{{main article|List of football clubs in Andorra}}

* Country: Andorra
* Football association: [[Andorran Football Federation]]
* Top-level league: [[Andorran First Division]] ({{lang-ca|Primera Divisió}})
* UEFA ranking: 53rd<ref name=coefficient2018/>
* Soccerway profile: [https://int.soccerway.com/national/andorra/ here]

Andorra's national league system was formed in 1993, and the Andorran Football Federation gained UEFA membership in 1996.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=and/index.html|title=Member associations: Andorra|publisher=UEFA|accessdate=10 August 2010}}</ref> Records from the league's first three seasons are incomplete, but FC Santa Coloma have won more First Division titles than any other team.<ref>CE Principat have three titles, and were runners-up in the 1993–94 season, meaning that they cannot match Santa Coloma's six confirmed league titles. {{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/andochamp.html|title=Andorra: List of champions|publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|accessdate=9 September 2012|date=31 May 2012|first=Igor|last=Kramarsic}}</ref>
Another Andorran football club, [[FC Andorra]], play in the [[Spanish football league system]]. In recent years, eight teams have competed in the First Division. Each team plays two matches against the other seven clubs. After fourteen games, the league splits into two groups, with teams carrying their previous points totals forward. The top four teams play each other a further two times in the championship round to decide 1st–4th places, while the bottom four teams do likewise in the relegation round, to determine the 5th–8th positions. At the end of the season, the bottom-placed team is relegated, while the seventh-placed team plays a two-legged play-off against the second-placed team in the [[Segona Divisió|Second Division]] to decide which team plays in which division for the following season.

