==Finland==
{{main article|List of football clubs in Finland}}

* Country: Finland
* Football association: [[Football Association of Finland]]
* Top-level league: [[Veikkausliiga|Finnish Premier League]] ({{lang-fi|Veikkausliiga}}, {{lang-sv|Tipsligan}})
* UEFA ranking: 38th<ref name=coefficient2018/>
* Soccerway profile: [https://int.soccerway.com/national/finland/ here]

Finland's current league has been contested annually since 1898, with the exceptions of 1914 and 1943.<ref name=finlandchamp>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesf/finchamp.html|title=Finland: List of champions|publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|accessdate=11 September 2001|date=7 May 2010|first=Heikki|last=Pietarinen}}</ref> The most successful team are HJK Helsinki with 22 titles; as of 2010, no other team has won 10 or more. However, between 1920 and 1948 a rival championship operated, organised by the [[Finnish Workers' Sports Federation]]. Frequent champions in that competition before it came under the jurisdiction of the Football Association of Finland included [[Kullervo Helsinki]], [[Vesa Helsinki]] and [[Tampereen Pallo-Veikot]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesf/fin-tulchamp.html|title=Finland: TUL champions|publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|accessdate=11 September 2010|date=21 May 2010|first=Heikki|last=Pietarinen}}</ref> The Premier League consists of 12 teams, which play one another three times each for a total of 33 matches. At the end of the season the bottom club is relegated to the [[Ykkönen|First Division]].

